            ## POsitioning System Ontology
            ### Introduction

            > POSO provides the terminologies needed to describe different **types of positioning systems**, the **algorithms** and technnologies
            that they implement and the **data** that is produced by these systems.
        {% endmarkdown %}

        <aside class="notes">
            So to quickly introduce you to POSO, it is a new ontology that provides you with the terminologies
            needed to describe the different types of positioning systems, the algorithms, tecnologies and
            techniques that they implement. And finally terminologies to describe the data they produce.
        </aside>
    </section>
</section>

