        ## Methodology
        1. Design constraints 
        2. First prototype <small>(IPIN 2022)</small>
        3. Object Relational Mapping for RDF with the POSO ontology
        4. Positioning systems with automatic data output to RDF using POSO
    {% endmarkdown %}

    <aside class="notes">
        Our methodology of the ontology design was based on our own generic positioning system named OpenHPS
        as well as existing datasets for positioning systems such as UJIndoorLoc or the EvAAL competition. 
        Our design constraints for the framework were very similar to the ontology.

        We created a first prototype for IPIN 2022 where we only used some of the core ontologies.
        We quickly realised that more work on the ontology aspect was needed which resulted us in creating
        a dedicated module for our own positioning framework where we use the POSO ontology.
